identificationModule.briefTitle: A Study to Evaluate the Long-Term Efficacy and Safety of Mirikizumab in Participants With Moderately to Severely Active Ulcerative Colitis (LUCENT 3)
identificationModule.officialTitle: A Phase 3, Multicenter, Open-Label Extension Study to Evaluate the Long Term Efficacy and Safety of Mirikizumab in Patients With Moderately to Severely Active Ulcerative Colitis LUCENT 3

descriptionModule.briefSummary: This study is designed to evaluate the long-term efficacy and safety of mirikizumab in participants with moderately to severely active ulcerative colitis (UC). The study will last up to 3 years. Participants who complete the 3-year study may continue to receive mirikizumab until it is (outside of this study) in their country or until they meet other discontinuation criteria.

primaryOutcomes.measure: Percentage of Participants in Clinical Remission
primaryOutcomes.description: Clinical remission based on the modified Mayo Score (MMS).

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Percentage of Participants in Endoscopic Remission
secondaryOutcomes.description: Endoscopic remission based on the MMS Endoscopic Subscore (ES).

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Percentage of Participants in Corticosteroid-free Remission
Percentage of Participants with Histologic-Endoscopic Mucosal Remission at Week 52
secondaryOutcomes.description: Endoscopic remission based on the MMS ES and histologic remission based on histologic disease activity index.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Health Related Quality of Life: Inflammatory Bowel Disease Questionnaire (IBDQ) Score
secondaryOutcomes.description: Health Related Quality of Life based on IBDQ score.
UC symptoms based on numeric rating score.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Percentage of Participants Who are Hospitalized Due to UC
secondaryOutcomes.description: Participants who are hospitalized due to UC.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Percentage of Participants Who Undergo UC Surgeries Including Colectomy
secondaryOutcomes.description: Participants who undergo UC surgeries including colectomy.

eligibilityModule.eligibilityCriteria:
* Inclusion Criteria

  * Participants from Study AMAC (NCT02589665) or AMBG (NCT03524092) who have had at least one study drug administration and have not had early termination of study drug.
  * Female participants must agree to contraception requirements.
* Exclusion Criteria

  * Participants must not have developed a new condition, including cancer in the originator study.
  * Participants must not have any important infections including, but not limited to, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, HIV/AIDS, and active tuberculosis (TB) during either originator study
  * Participants may not have received surgery for UC in the originator study or are likely to require surgery for treatment of UC during the study.
  * Participants must not have developed adenomatous polyps during the originator study that have not been removed prior to the start of this study.

ipdSharingStatementModule.description:
Lilly provides access to the individual patient data from studies on approved medicines and indications as defined by the sponsor specific information on ClinicalStudyDataRequest.com.

This access is provided in a timely fashion after the primary publication is accepted. Researchers need to have an approved research proposal submitted through ClinicalStudyDataRequest.com. Access to the data will be provided in a secure data sharing environment after signing a data sharing agreement.
